              "date": "2026-03-08T23:42:05Z"
            }
          ],
          "series_items": [],
          "patch_summary": "This patch addresses a warning in the RAID0 driver caused by large allocations exceeding MAX_PAGE_ORDER, leading to a WARN_ON_ONCE_GFP condition. The patch converts strip_zone and devlist allocations from kzalloc/kzalloc_objs to kvzalloc/kvfree, which first attempts contiguous allocation with __GFP_NOWARN and falls back to vmalloc for large sizes.",
